A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Lynne Riley on the occasion of her retirement; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Lynne Riley has long been recognized by the citizens of this state for her
4 character, leadership, and commitment to the betterment and welfare of Georgia families; and
5 WHEREAS, Lynne Riley has dutifully served the people of Georgia for 21 years as a Fulton
6 County Commissioner, State Representative, Revenue Commissioner, State Treasurer, and
7 President of the Georgia Student Finance Commission; and
8 WHEREAS, over $4.3 billion has been awarded to 459,408 students through the HOPE
9 Scholarship Program since Lynne Riley was appointed by Governor Brian P. Kemp to serve
10 as President of the Georgia Student Finance Commission in July 2020; and
11 WHEREAS, her creativity and vision played a vital role in implementing the GEORGIA
12 MATCH program, one of the largest state-run direct admissions programs in the nation; and
13 WHEREAS, Lynne Riley was the first woman to be appointed Georgia State Treasurer and
14 Georgia State Revenue Commissioner; and
